SGB SAYS HAPPY WITH CURRENT PORTFOLIO . Belgian holding company Societe Generale de Belgique SA ( SGB ) said on Wednesday it was happy with its current portfolio of six major holdings . SGB chairman Etienne Davignon told a news conference he saw no reason to change it . The six core stakes are Tractebel , Generale Bank , Fortis AG , Union Miniere ( UM ) , Recticel and Sagem . Earlier this month chief executive officer Philippe Liotier was quoted as saying the stakes in UM and Recticel " were not forever . " " Eternity is a philosophical concept , " Davignon said . People had been wrong to conclude that UM and Recticel would be sold in the coming months . " Our portfolio will continue as is . " - - Brussels Newsroom + 32 2 287 6810 , Fax + 32 2 230 7710 
